text: Ellicott High School is a public high school in Ellicott, Colorado, United States. It is part of the Ellicott School District 22. == Athletics == === Teams === Ellicott's athletic teams are nicknamed the Thunderhawks and the school's colors are purple, gold, and white. Ellicott teams compete in the following sports: * Baseball * Basketball * Boy's soccer * Cross Country * Football * Volleyball * Track * Wrestling * Girl's soccer === State championships === * Girl's basketball ** 1994 Colorado AA State Championshttps://www2.chsaa.org/about/pdf/Champions_by_School.pdf ** 1995 Colorado AA State Championshttps://www.denverpost.com/2013/01/09/all-time- list-of-colorado-girls-high-school-basketball-champions/ == References == == External links == * Category:Schools in El Paso County, Colorado Category:Public high schools in Colorado
